{"parse":{"title":"Metz Epitome","pageid":29997701,"revid":849942349,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <i><b>Metz Epitome</b></i> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Late_antiquity\" title=\"Late antiquity\">late antiquity</a> summary of earlier <a href=\"/wiki/Historical\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Historical\">historical</a> fragments and covers the <a href=\"/wiki/Conquest_(military)\" title=\"Conquest (military)\">conquests</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/Alexander_the_great\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Alexander the great\">Alexander the great</a>  between <a href=\"/wiki/Hyrcania\" title=\"Hyrcania\">Hyrcania</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Punjab_region\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Punjab region\">northwest India</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Loube_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Loube-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Worthington_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Worthington-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The only surviving manuscript was found in <a href=\"/wiki/Metz\" title=\"Metz\">Metz</a>, from which the text's name originates. The manuscript was destroyed during the Second World War, but there are two transcriptions of the original. The Epitome was part of the same manuscript as the so-called Liber de Morte Alexandri Magni Testamentumque (which may have been written by the same epitomator, as suggested by E. Baynham).\n</p><p>The sources of the <a href=\"/wiki/Anonymous_work\" title=\"Anonymous work\">anonymous author</a> have much in common with the historian <a href=\"/wiki/Cleitarchus\" title=\"Cleitarchus\">Cleitarchus</a>, through the writings of <a href=\"/wiki/Diodorus_Siculus\" title=\"Diodorus Siculus\">Diodorus Siculus</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Quintus_Curtius_Rufus\" title=\"Quintus Curtius Rufus\">Quintus Curtius Rufus</a>. Non-Cleitarchan elements in the <a href=\"/wiki/Manuscript\" title=\"Manuscript\">text</a> seem to reflect a certain <a href=\"/wiki/Judaism\" title=\"Judaism\">Hebraic</a> view concerning Alexander.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Loube_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Loube-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Worthington_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Worthington-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <i>Epitome</i> paints a unique portrait of Alexander and includes some information not found elsewhere but in view of its late authorship and the few additional historical fact it offers, the value of the <i>Metz Epitome</i> lies in its interpretation of Alexander's career rather than as a source for it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Loube_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Loube-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Metz_Epitome&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Baynham, Elizabeth and Yardley, J. (1997) <i>The Historiography of Alexander the Great: The Metz Epitome</i>. University of Newcastle 2000.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Baynham, E.(1995) <i>An Introduction to the Metz Epitome: its Traditions and Value</i>, Antichthon 29, 1995,</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Loube-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Loube_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Loube_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Loube_3-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ruor.uottawa.ca/en/handle/10393/10107\">Loube, Heather The (1995) \"Metz Epitome\": Alexander (July, 330 B.C.-July, 325 B.C.) A commentary. University Ottawa ON Canada </a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Worthington-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Worthington_4-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Worthington_4-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Worthington, Ian (2003) <i>Alexander the Great: a reader</i>. page 10 <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=-qYOAAAAQAAJ&amp;pg=PA10&amp;lpg=PA10&amp;dq=metz+epitome&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=cQTs3T4EWj&amp;sig=Q5yipiJDpL8oysbHZcsGPzujD7U&amp;hl=en&amp;ei=dPoBTcKCK8jorAfKjLGRDw&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;ct=result&amp;resnum=2&amp;ved=0CBcQ6AEwATgK#v=onepage&amp;q=metz%20epitome&amp;f=false\">[1]</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Continent_m%C3%A9ridional_austral_ou_Antarctique_(Description_de_l%27Univers,_V,_pl._107).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/71/Continent_m%C3%A9ridional_austral_ou_Antarctique_%28Description_de_l%27Univers%2C_V%2C_pl._107%29.jpg/35px-Continent_m%C3%A9ridional_austral_ou_Antarctique_%28Description_de_l%27Univers%2C_V%2C_pl._107%29.jpg\" width=\"35\" height=\"47\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/71/Continent_m%C3%A9ridional_austral_ou_Antarctique_%28Description_de_l%27Univers%2C_V%2C_pl._107%29.jpg/53px-Continent_m%C3%A9ridional_austral_ou_Antarctique_%28Description_de_l%27Univers%2C_V%2C_pl._107%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/71/C